We kicked off construction this week on a full floor, unfinished basement for this lovely 4-peat client in the western burbs.  There's going to be a beautiful bathroom, a fitness room, a Guest Room with a super fun (and practical) bunk situation, a Wet Bar, and 3 separate niches for lounging....it's going to be a GAMECHANGER for this young family! 

It's been super fun to work on different design projects for the same clients over the years and over different phases of their lives.  Swipe for the progression!

Phase 1: Bedrooms in her Wicker Park condo (pre-marriage)
Phase 2: Primary Bedroom and Living Spaces in their beautiful new home in Western Springs (married, pre-baby)
Phase 3: Super fun Nursery for Baby (they kept the sex a secret + fun element is we were pregnant at the same time and had babies 2 weeks apart 🥹)
Phase 4: Full Basement Buildout for this family of 3 👨‍👩‍👦

Happy 8️⃣th birthday to this little business that's not so little anymore! 🎉I'm continuously amazed by our talented team, vendors, and amazing clients. 

What started as one-off room projects has evolved into complex, full-home renovations and project management (and many times, with the same clients from way-back when 🤗)

The duality and roller coaster of emotions that go into this work is bonkers. It’s very much a IYKYK situation….but 2 questions to keep in mind: 

Question 1: Are there super hard days where nothing seems to go right (and maybe my morning is particularly challenging bc #toddlerlife)? 😂

Yes. 😵‍💫

Question 2: Are there super amazing days where you see all that hard work pay off? ⚡️

Hells Yes. 👊

(as long as the answer to question # 2 is in the strong affirmative - we're gonna keep doin' what we're doin'. Thx for following along our journey! ✌🏼)

Our “Jordan Year” (‘23) has come and gone....what were some of the highlights for you❓

I didn’t create a 2023 recap reel, or do a Top Nine (I watched and loved everyone else’s from my bed while I was knocked out with a sinus infection over the Holidays...)

So here are some of our team’s top highlights from 2023: 
- Completed one of our most extensive full gut + furnishing projects (more to come on this....) 🤗
- Had one of our favorite transformations (#RiverNorthResidence) featured in a large spread with @designchicagomag 📖
- Got our beautiful Sprinter van “MOJO” in the mix - we are now super mobile and able to better serve our Clients 🚙
- Photographed lots of fun projects to share with y’all here (photoshoots are a big lift + investment.....very much a IYKYK situation) 📸
- Hosted a super festive Client Appreciation Summer Fete at the Chicago Club 🥂
- Visited High Point Spring Market for the first time (I always had a baby or a global pandemic crampin’ my style previously!) 🛋️
- Welcomed another talented Designer Hannah to our team 🙋🏻‍♀️
- Our talented Designer Geremy welcomed a beautiful baby girl Layla to the world 👼🏼
- We had fun working hard + playing hard 💥

2024 is off to a great start already!
